==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Munch
<hw>Munch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Munched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Munching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Prob. akin to
<ets>mumble</ets>: cf. also F. <ets>manger</ets> to eat (cf.
<er>Mange</er>), and <ets>m⟦acir⟧cher</ets> to cher (cf.
<er>Masticate</er>). See <er>Mumble</er>.]</ety> <def>To chew with a
grinding, crunching sound, as a beast chews provender; to chew
deliberately or in large mouthfuls.</def> <altsp>[Formerly written also
<asp>maunch</asp> and <asp>mounch</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I could <qex>munch</qex> your good dry oats.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Munchausenism</ent>⟦br⟧
